1. npm init : whenever you are starting a new project. it helps create file that helps to run the project (package.json)

2. node <filename>: runs the files

3. npm init -y: creates a node.js project by skipping questions an creates a package.json file with default values

4. npm install url : url package

5. npm install : install node modules

6. npm install @types/

7. npm i express : express package

8. npm uninstall url : uninstall url package

9. npm i --global nodemon, nodemon index.js

10. npm i express@4.17.2: used to specify which version of express you wanna install (4.17.2 doesnot mean anything here, its just an example, watch "versioning in nodejs" by piyush garg incase of confusion)

11. npm update: updates packages on the basis of specified version range

